goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify any extreme values in the flight count data that may need further investigation.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='count', bins=50, color='blue', kde=True)
    median_count = data['count'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_count, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_count:.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Flight Counts')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight counts between origin and destination airports?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).sum().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values('count', ascending=False).head(10)
    chart = sns.barplot(x='origin', y='count', hue='destination', data=data)
    plt.title('Which origin and destination airports have the highest number of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Destination', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='count', data=data)
    plt.axvline(data['count'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['count'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.title('What is the average number of flights between origin and destination airports?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    sns.boxplot(x=data['count'], ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('Are there any outliers in the flight count data?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Flight Counts')
    plt.legend(title='Flight Counts', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from geopy.distance import great_circle

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Calculate the distance between origin and destination airports
    data['distance'] = data.apply(lambda row: great_circle((row['origin_lat'], row['origin_lon']), (row['destination_lat'], row['destination_lon'])).miles, axis=1)

    # Create a scatter plot of flight counts vs distance
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='distance', y='count', alpha=0.5)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between flight counts and distance between origin and destination airports?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    plt.ylabel('Flight Counts')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
